The Ebonyi State chapter of the All Progressives Congress (APC) has conducted councillorship primaries across the 171 wards in the State ahead of July 30, 2022, local government elections in the State. Speaking with Journalists shortly after distributing the primary election materials on Thursday at the Party’s secretariat, Abakaliki, the chairman of the APC in the State, Chief Stanley Okoro Emegha, expressed optimism about a hitch-free congress. Emegha said that every machinery had been put in place to ensure the success of the exercise. “As you can see, every machinery is in place, the security agencies are fully notified, and you can see their presence. This is to make sure that it is a free and fair election, “Absolutely there is no crack in the party, it’s a free for all contest, everyone is allowed to go to the field, but the party is looking for a popular candidate to win elections because of the upcoming general election”, Emegha said. Also in an interview, the Speaker of Ebonyi State House of Assembly and governorship candidate of the APC in the State, Hon Francis Ogbonna Nwifuru, praised the peaceful conduct of the exercise. Nwifuru called on the stakeholders to close ranks to ensure that APC emerged victorious in the upcoming local government council elections. “This is an internal party affair; the party at the ward level is in charge of today’s function, and the state and local governments have also done what they are supposed to do. This is a grassroot issue, and if its not properly organized, then we will have a lot of fracases which we wouldn’t want. POLL “And you know Ebonyi is purely APC state, and that is why we hammered once on unifying the party leaders and to get everybody on board, and make sure that everything happens in a peaceful manner”. Our Correspondent who monitored the exercise reports that only 39 out of the 171 wards were contested, others emerged unopposed